Privacy Policy

Thank you for using Travel CarbonCount!
This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our carbon footprint calculation services. By accessing or using our app, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.

1- Information We Collect:

We collect information about your travel activities, including but not limited to distance traveled, modes of transportation, vehicle specifics, fuel consumption, and hotel stays.
Personal information such as your name, email address, or other identifiers may be collected if provided voluntarily.

2- How We Use Your Information:

We use the collected information to accurately estimate the greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions of your trips.
Your personal information may be used to provide you with relevant updates, improvements, or important notices regarding our app.

3- Data Accuracy and Compliance:

Our carbon footprint calculations adhere to the GHG Protocol standards, ensuring compliance and reliability.
We utilize DEFRA conversion factors, updating them annually, to guarantee accuracy in emissions assessments.
Our app comprehensively measures emissions across all three scopes and considers various transportation modes (air, sea, train, or road) to provide precise carbon footprint calculations.

4- Environmental Impact Assessment:

We analyze factors such as distance, vehicle specifics, fuel consumption, and hotel stays to ensure a comprehensive and accurate assessment of the environmental impact of your journey.

5- Data Security:

We take reasonable steps to protect your information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure.
While we strive to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.

6- Commitment to Trustworthiness:

We are committed to delivering trustworthy and detailed carbon footprint calculations for your complete travel journey.
We are continually working on advancing our tool to make it more comprehensive and accurate.

7- Updates and Changes:

We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons.
It is your responsibility to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

8- Contact Us:

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at ali@al-burraq.com
By continuing to use Travel CarbonCount, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy.

Al-Burraq Technologies
